<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Yes, but again game engine punihes you with restrictions/punishments, not by GM, which is good!</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tarquin">Tarquin</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:18 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Yes, but again game engine punihes you with restrictions/punishments, not by GM, which is good!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=697" TARGET=_self>Re: Nicely said but don't start to judge just like that on PKilling..</A> (Geiger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> A prime example of killing out of role would be a Human Paladin

<BR>&gt; man Killing a Human Paladin Female 5 lvls below him. That is a
<BR>&gt; somewhate stretched example however, I personally won't accept
<BR>&gt; the "I'm role playing a vicious Psycho Paladin Domestic
<BR>&gt; Violence oriented Murderer". Rules will be built around
<BR>&gt; PvP, the closer we come to fine tune Role PLaying PvP the less
<BR>&gt; restrictions I forsee being on PvP. This game doesn't inherently
<BR>&gt; support sensless killing and althout it may happen in certain
<BR>&gt; cases, I believe most will agree that it will be dealt with in
<BR>&gt; some way shape or fasion. Time will tell what happens.
<P>Yes, thats why its nice to make a game engine that sorta molds Everquest in way you want it...after this is done, I don't want to be consulted and brainwashed by GM who thinks paladin can't kill a paladin.. make restriction if you wanna do this, but don't come to me when I kill one and say don't do it again..and I do it again and then you PERSONALLY punish my character...
<P>(not reffering to you, just using you as an example for GM)..
<P>Game engine should have its own mechanics on whats frowned upon and whats not... rather than GM controlled :P I was very glad when I heard GM's won't award good roleplayers, and this is an excellent decision!
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
